OL,6,FInvestigations into those allegations
OL,7,Fconcluded without a definitive outcome
OL,8,Fand parole considerations resumed in
OL,9,FMay and June this year.
OL,11,FThese are still ongoing after the
OL,12,Fboard ruled it needed an extra day to
OL,13,Fhear all the evidence. This had been
OL,14,Fexpected to take place in June, but a
OL,15,Fbereavement suffered by a member of
OL,16,Fthe board saw further postponement.
OL,17,FNow, that final hearing is set to take
OL,18,Fplace on Friday (3 October).
