OL,3,CDouble child-killer Colin Pitchfork to
OL,4,Cface new parole hearing this week
OL,6,F"My view remains that Mr Pitchfork,
OL,7,Fgiven the heinous nature of his crimes
OL,8,Fand that he is in his mid-60s, is too
OL,9,Fdangerous to be released. He has
OL,10,Finstilled fear and cast a dark shadow
OL,11,Fover an otherwise peaceful community.
OL,13,F"I would fear for the safety of young
OL,14,Fwomen if he were released, it is not a
OL,15,Fgamble I would be willing to make.
